@dmonett @PDillis @Grady_Booch No. These systems *learn* from existing art.
If a piece such a system produces copies or reproduces an existing piece by another artist, that constitutes copyright infringement.
But if the piece is merely *inspired* by other artists, then it's the same as what human artists do.

