@pfau @kchonyc @McAllesterDavid Slow Feature Analysis is very much a *non-contrastive* method.
It does *not* use negative samples to prevent collapse.
Instead, it maximizes the information content of the representation by maintaining the variance and decorrelating the variables, like VICReg and BarlowTwins.

