@mpshanahan @rgblong @davidchalmers42 There is an underlying reality that the text used for training describes.
It's just that much of this underlying reality is largely inaccessible from the text only.
Text is too discrete, too approximate, and too low bandwidth, to allow an agent to learn an appropriate world model

@davidchalmers42 - World model (including a model of self), 
- objectives (some hardwired, some trainable, some configurable), and 
- a mechanism for inferring sequences of actions that optimize the objective given the predictions of the world model.

